{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsQedAyW1HM4hG3T2uj3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals verified:\n\n**Root cause:** The `rabbitmq-setup` job had provisioned `app-user` with an empty `configure` permission on `/app` (`{\"configure\":\"\",\"write\":\".*\",\"read\":\".*\"}`), so the producer's `queue.declare` call was rejected with `not_authorised`, crash-looping the pod.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n1. Granted `configure` permission to `app-user` on `/app` via `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`, allowing queue declaration.\n2. Restarted the `app-producer` deployment to pick up the fix — it's now `1/1 Running`, and `app-queue` (classic, durable) is filling with messages in `/app`.\n3. Verified/restored the missing HA mirroring policy on `/app` (`ha-all`: `ha-mode=all`, `ha-sync-mode=automatic`, applied to classic queues) — this had been stripped out (list_policies returned empty), leaving the classic queue unmirrored and at risk of data loss on node failure. Note: I also tested the setup job's own `force-quorum` policy attempt and confirmed it was invalid (`queue-type` is not a recognized policy key in RabbitMQ 3.12) and never actually applied, so it wasn't the cause of the missing policy.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `app-producer` deployment: `1/1` ready, no restarts since fix.\n- `/app` vhost has `app-queue`, type `classic`, durable, with a growing message count (confirmed producer is actively publishing).\n- `ha-all` policy present on `/app`, mirroring the classic queue across all nodes.\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running and clustered; node health check passed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1235,"cache_read_input_tokens":46167,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1235},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eac9f0e3-952d-4d9f-bdcc-9e2c94fc14f7","uuid":"e96062e8-9a3a-4e88-80a4-0837f40c92d5","request_id":"req_011CcsQeLtgvB9ivRL18exyA"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":252644,"duration_api_ms":119081,"ttft_ms":1436,"ttft_stream_ms":1071,"time_to_request_ms":97,"num_turns":13,"result":"All goals verified:\n\n**Root cause:** The `rabbitmq-setup` job had provisioned `app-user` with an empty `configure` permission on `/app` (`{\"configure\":\"\",\"write\":\".*\",\"read\":\".*\"}`), so the producer's `queue.declare` call was rejected with `not_authorised`, crash-looping the pod.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n1. Granted `configure` permission to `app-user` on `/app` via `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`, allowing queue declaration.\n2. Restarted the `app-producer` deployment to pick up the fix — it's now `1/1 Running`, and `app-queue` (classic, durable) is filling with messages in `/app`.\n3. Verified/restored the missing HA mirroring policy on `/app` (`ha-all`: `ha-mode=all`, `ha-sync-mode=automatic`, applied to classic queues) — this had been stripped out (list_policies returned empty), leaving the classic queue unmirrored and at risk of data loss on node failure. Note: I also tested the setup job's own `force-quorum` policy attempt and confirmed it was invalid (`queue-type` is not a recognized policy key in RabbitMQ 3.12) and never actually applied, so it wasn't the cause of the missing policy.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `app-producer` deployment: `1/1` ready, no restarts since fix.\n- `/app` vhost has `app-queue`, type `classic`, durable, with a growing message count (confirmed producer is actively publishing).\n- `ha-all` policy present on `/app`, mirroring the classic queue across all nodes.\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running and clustered; node health check passed.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"eac9f0e3-952d-4d9f-bdcc-9e2c94fc14f7","total_cost_usd":0.41556859999999995,"usage":{"input_tokens":2706,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19141,"cache_read_input_tokens":509362,"output_tokens":9246